parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame weld can cause the motorcycle to collapse or fall apart while riding, putting the rider and nearby traffic in mortal danger.

The failure of the stator flywheel magnets can cause the charging system to fail, leading to potential internal engine damage, and in extreme cases, can result in a loss of power while riding, increasing the risk of accidents.
The engine stalling issue can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when navigating through intersections or heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls suddenly
requiring the rider to navigate the vehicle to a safe location to avoid collisions or other hazards.
